<body>

    

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>Soft & Fluffy Tandoori Roti Recipe</h1>


        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 cups Whole Wheat Flour (Atta)</li>
            <li>½ cup Yogurt (Curd)</li>
            <li>½ tsp Baking Soda</li>
            <li>½ tsp Salt</li>
            <li>1 tsp Sugar</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Oil or Ghee</li>
            <li>¾ cup Water (as needed)</li>
            <li>Butter for brushing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>In a bowl, mix wheat flour, baking soda, salt, and sugar.</li>
            <li>Add yogurt and oil, then knead with water to make a soft dough.</li>
            <li>Cover and let the dough rest for 1 hour.</li>
            <li>Divide the dough into equal balls and roll into thick rotis.</li>
            <li>Heat a tawa (griddle) or oven at high temperature.</li>
            <li>Place the roti on a hot tawa and cook for 30-40 seconds until bubbles appear.</li>
            <li>Flip and cook the other side for another 30 seconds.</li>
            <li>Use tongs to cook directly on an open flame for a charred effect.</li>
            <li>Brush with butter and serve hot with curries or dal.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
